  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>GE Profile — feature-focused premium within Haier-owned GE</h2>
    <p>GE Profile occupies the feature-focused premium tier within GE Appliances' wall oven lineup. Positioning: above mainstream GE (where competition is price + basic feature set) and below GE Café (style-first premium) + GE Monogram (ultra-luxury). Profile's feature set emphasizes cooking technology (True European Convection + Air Fry mode), smart integration (SmartHQ Wi-Fi + app), and practical premium features rather than aesthetic differentiation. For LA customers, Profile fits at the $1.5-5k wall oven spec — customers who wanted more than base mass-market but aren't buying at the luxury or aesthetic-premium tier.</p>
    <p>Haier Group acquired GE Appliances in 2016 from General Electric Company. GE Appliances continues operating from Appliance Park in Louisville, Kentucky, with Haier ownership bringing investment in modernization without disrupting the US manufacturing and distribution footprint. For LA service, Profile parts run through Louisville distribution with typical 2-4 day lead on common service components, 3-5 days on specialty current-generation components.</p>
  </div></section>

